						<summary>

						<p>On a stone planted by the side of the Uttarēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the praise of a certain Guṇḍa, the grandson of • • • Pallava, his wife Jayāṁ bikā and their son Sōma, who is described as Pallavānvayāditya. Further it mentions construction of a temple at Dhūlipāla by Āditya and made several gifts of land for providing services. Mentions Aniyaṅka-Bhīma and Vēṅgi.</p>						

						</summary>
